    "body": "> Windows also has meta key, which is Windows key. Not sure about Linux.\n\nIs it ? I thought meta was alt. \n\nShortcut with `alt` conflict with typing letters (as with shift).\nWindows+key is a strange shortcut user will not be used to, but we don't prevent them from binding to it. \n\nI missed the fact that you were explicitely asking about `ctrl-s` as save I tought you were using to speek of `ctrl-smth` shortcut in general. I don't see any reason why `ctrl-s` and `cmd-s` shouldn't both save.\n"
